{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"302d7504-82cc-4ef9-b3f3-6019c801ab3f","content":"No existing files found in the working directory. Since this is a general guidance request, here's exactly what to do:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nOn the `ContentPage` root element, add the `x:DataType` attribute pointing to your ViewModel:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Entry Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" Placeholder=\"Theme\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Stepper Value=\"{Binding FontSize}\" Minimum=\"8\" Maximum=\"48\" />\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\nThat's the only XAML change needed — every `{Binding}` inside the page is now **compiled** against `SettingsViewModel` at build time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nCompiled bindings already emit **build errors** if a property name is misspelled or the type is wrong (e.g., `{Binding Themee}` → **XC0045**).\n\nTo make sure nothing slips through, also add this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <!-- Treat binding warnings/errors as build errors -->\n  <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n| Topic | Detail |\n|---|---|\n| **How it works** | `x:DataType` tells the XAML compiler the expected type, so it resolves properties at compile time instead of reflection at runtime. |\n| **Performance** | Compiled bindings are faster — they generate direct property access code instead of using reflection. |\n| **Opt-out locally** | Use `x:DataType=\"\"` on a child element if you need an untyped binding in a specific subtree (e.g., for `BindingContext` changes in a `DataTemplate`). |\n| **Error code** | `XC0045` = \"Binding: Property not found on type\". With `WarningsAsErrors` this becomes a hard build failure. |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"33a4a04e-2464-426a-afcc-248183e9411c","outputTokens":627},"id":"8406db02-4e63-4971-9c81-22d30fbe0c66","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:59:00.141Z","parentId":"929d3b07-8c07-4ba6-8b58-423b11107820"}
